This directory contains the configuration of the Buildroot 2025.11.2 which I used to test mth vugpio.py
Unpack the Buildroot there, copy BR.config as .config to the Buildroot directory.
Then do "make" in that directory.

The script start-qemu-gpio.sh is a modified version of the start-qemu.sh generated by Buildroot.
Just the section:

-object memory-backend-memfd,id=mem,size=512M,share=on \
-chardev socket,id=gpio,path=/tmp/gpio.sock \
-device vhost-user-gpio-pci,chardev=gpio \

has been added to the QEMU arguments.
